fields.name: Russell House Tavern
fields.address: 14 John F. Kennedy St, Cambridge, MA 02138

fields.name: Breakfast Egg Sandwich
fields.review: So good! One of my go-to's for a midday sandwich.

fields.name: Muesli (Cup)
fields.review: Very healthy and nutritious. Great granola, fruit, and chia seeds. Blueberries were a little soft. Feeling energized!

fields.name: K-Town Throwdown
fields.review: Tangy chicken with sesame on rice makes my mouth water. Scallions super fresh, broccoli provides a nice crunch. I get this bowl at least once a week.

fields.name: Niko Pita
fields.review: Pretty good. Flavorful tzatziki and chicken. French fries could be crunchier. Sometimes gets soggy when ordered away.

fields.name: Double-Smoked Bacon, Cheddar & Egg Sandwich
fields.review: LOVE! Affordable and very filling. Flaky croissant bread with crispy bacon. Speedy service as well.

fields.name: Pizza
fields.review: Delicious pizza!

fields.name: The Edelman
fields.review: It was such a delicious burger -- I would highly recommend!

fields.name: Tomato Basil Pizza
fields.review: Great for a late night stop. Not as great for a full meal. Delicious but quite greasy.

fields.name: Katerina Pita
fields.review: I was really missing Mediterranean food, so I was so happy to find this place in Harvard Square!

fields.name: Cereal Milk Ice Cream
fields.review: Honestly the most delicious ice cream I've ever had. It was very expensive, but so worth it. Highly recommend if visiting Harvard!

fields.name: Harvest Bowl
fields.review: This was really filling. There was a long line and it took a while to get the food, but overall this salad was great. It made me feel healthy and ready to go for the rest of my day. Add chicken if you want some extra protein.

fields.name: Gyoza Combo
fields.review: Such good ramen and gyoza. Ramen had authentic toppings, but a little out of my comfort zone, so I removed them. Ordered a second serving of gyoza because it was so good!

fields.name: Shack Burger
fields.review: Honestly not a fan -- the wait took FOREVER and the food wasn't even that good. The cashier got into a huge fight with someone else which made the whole environment tense inside. Portions were small and not that good.

fields.name: Micro original with strawberries topping
fields.review: My favorite! I spend way too much money here. Sweet and tart. Very refreshing desert.

fields.name: Vanilla Iced Latte
fields.review: Super good but finished in just a few sips. Not worth it for high coffee price!

fields.name: Souvlaki Classic
fields.review: Pretty good. Love the different components of the dish. Some fat on the chicken. Wish it had more fries!

fields.name: Margherita Pizza
fields.review: For an Italian restaurant, this was pretty bad! Not cooked enough so the mozzarella was raw. Hard chunks of cheese made the pizza pretty bad.

fields.name: Popover
fields.review: A-M-A-Z-I-N-G! They run out quick, so you have to grab one early in the morning. Light, flaky, gooey inside. Perfect with a side of Clover's apple butter.

fields.name: The LeBron James
fields.review: Wow! So many flavors in this. A little hard to eat, but you can never go wrong with Mr. Bartley's.

fields.name: Black and White Malted Milkshake
fields.review: An average black and white milkshake. Great size portions. Sorta wish it had a little more to it.

fields.name: Momofuku
fields.review: This is heaven on earth. Slightly crunchy on the border and soft as a cloud on the inside. Takes sweetness to a whole new level.

fields.name: Fruit Delight
fields.review: Delicious dessert! Very sweet, maybe too sweet? Make sure you have plenty of room in your stomachthe waffle and toppings are quite heavy.

fields.name: Turkey Avocado
fields.review: Yum! So many good flavors in this one. Very filling and nutritious. A little difficult and messy to eat. Also there was a very long line and wait.

fields.name: Speculoos Latte
fields.review: The flavoring is Belgian cookie butter. Perfect on a cold winter day.

fields.name: Bacon, Egg, & Fig
fields.review: An adventurous Sunday morning delicacy.
